---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Assetgrid.app">
	<main>
		<section class="landing">
			<div class="wrapper grid-parent">
				<div class="grid"></div>
				<div class="title">
					<h1>Control your personal finances</h1>
					<h2>See the big picture with Assetgrid</h2>
					<div class="buttons">
						<a href="/get-started" class="button is-primary">Install now</a>
						<a href="/reference" class="button">Reference</a>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="image">
					<img src="happy-money.svg" />
					<a href="http://www.freepik.com" class="image-attribution">Image by pch.vector / Freepik</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
		<div class="dark-divider"></div>
		<section class="about">
			<div class="wrapper narrow">
				<h2>What is Assetgrid?</h2>
				<p>Assetgrid is a personal finance dashboard.</p>
				<p>Many personal finance tools are centered around budgets and require you to organize your finances around that.
					Assetgrid is first and foremost a tool to collect and organize your personal finance data. How you want to explore your financial data is up to you.</p>
				<p>Assetgrid will soon support budgets, but it will also allow you to see how much money you spent on pizza the last 3 months,
					or find a receipt from a purchase you made and need to return, or keep track of whether or not your roommate has paid rent this month.</p>
				<p>This will be achieved through a combination of several systems.
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Metadata</strong>. Add any information you want to your transactions, be it images, documents, text or relations to other transactions and accounts.</li>
						<li><strong>Automation</strong>. Assetgrid allows you to create rules to automatically categorize and process your data.</li>
						<li><strong>A powerful query engine</strong> and flexible reports. Assetgrid will let you query your finances in any way you want and store those queries in reports for quick access.</li>
					</ul>
				</p>
			</div>
			<div class="horizontal-columns"></div>
		</section>
		<div class="dark-divider"></div>
		<section class="features">
			<h2>Features</h2>
			<div class="feature">
				<div class="text">
					<h3>Overview</h3>
					<p>See how your net worth develops over time, what you spend your money on, your sources of income or any other statistic you may want to know about your finances.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="image">
					<img src="screenshots/overview.png" />
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="feature">
				<div class="text">
					<h3>Powerful CSV importer</h3>
					<p>Most banks allow exporting your bank statement as a CSV file. Assetgrid has a powerful import tool, which will help you no matter what archaic standard your bank organizes the file in.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="image">
					<img src="screenshots/csv_import.png" />
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="feature">
				<div class="text">
					<h3>Categorize your transactions</h3>
					<p>Understand how you spend or earn your money by organizing it into categories.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="image">
					<img src="screenshots/categories.png" />
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="feature">
				<div class="text">
					<h3>Automation</h3>
					<p>Don't waste your time manually processing every transaction. Configure Assetgrid to do it for you.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="image">
					<img src="screenshots/automation.png" />
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="feature">
				<div class="text">
					<h3>Split transactions</h3>
					<p>Transactions with multiple lines are natively supported by Assetgrid, so you can enter in receipts or invoices without losing any information.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="image">
					<img src="screenshots/split_transaction.png" />
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="feature">
				<div class="text">
					<h3>Search</h3>
					<p>At the core of Assetgrid is our powerful search engine that let's you query your transaction in any way imaginable.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="image">
					<img src="screenshots/search.png" />
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
		<section class="upcoming">
			<div class="wrapper narrow">
				<h2>Upcoming features</h2>
				<p>Assetgrid is still in it's infancy, so it's basic at the moment. But we're moving fast and have a lot planned for the future.</p>

